com.sun.media.jsdt.http

Interface JSDTSocketInfo


  • public interface JSDTSocketInfo
    JSDTSocketInfo is an interface that extensions of the java.net.Socket class may use to provide more information on its capabilities. Based on the sun.rmi.transport.proxy.RMISocketInfo class.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean isReusable()
      Return true if this socket can be used for more than one JSDT call.
      void setReusable(boolean reusable)
      Sets an indication of whether this socket is reusable.

    • Method Detail

      • isReusable

        boolean isReusable()
        Return true if this socket can be used for more than one JSDT call. If a socket does not implement this interface, then it is assumed to be reusable.
        Returns:
        whether this socket is reusable.

      • setReusable

        void setReusable(boolean reusable)
        Sets an indication of whether this socket is reusable.
        Parameters:
        reusable - true if socket is reusable.
